			<td class="subhead">Jimmy&nbsp;Schaeffler</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td><b>Chairman, CSO and Senior Research,&nbsp;Carmel Group</b></td>
		</tr>
		
		
		
			<td><br>Jimmy Schaeffler is the chairman and CSO of The Carmel Group, a telecommunications, computer, and media industries consultant, conference organizer and publisher. The Carmel Group provides these services to a broad clientele in the private, public, government, and non-profit sectors. <br><br>
While being widely sought for its expertise on satellite TV, cable, wireless, and telephony, The Carmel Group has already earned a position as a leading authority on such new, advanced cable, telco, DBS, broadband and broadcast services as video-on-demand, digital video recorders, high-definition TV, satellite radio, and digital signage, to name just a few.<br><br>
Today, scores of the world's largest telecommunications, computer, and media companies seek Mr. Schaeffler’s insights for studies and conferences, etc., and his views are reported regularly in such publications as <i>Investor's Business Daily</i>, <i>Business Week</i>, <i>Time</i>magazine and <i>The Wall Street Journal</i>. Mr. Schaeffler is the author of numerous telecom books, and has been a frequent participant in CES conferences and activities, going back to the mid 1990s. A “google” of his name delivers literally thousands of entries.<br><br>
 Mr. Schaeffler holds a bachelor’s degree, with honors, from the University of California, Berkeley, and a J.D. degree from the University of Pacific, McGeorge School of Law in Sacramento, CA, where he served on the Pacific Law Journal. He is licensed to practice in CA, MN, CO, Washington, DC and before the U.S. Supreme Court. <br><br>
</td>
		</tr>
		
